OL,3,C20 Days in Mariupol: Nurse recounts
OL,4,Cfinal days before Russian occupation
OL,6,FThey were used to treating adult
OL,7,Fpatients in emergency situations - but
OL,8,Fchildren with shrapnel wounds and
OL,9,Fmissing limps was new territory for
OL,10,Fthem.
OL,12,F"There were no emotions, everyone was
OL,13,Fworking...and doing their job.
OL,14,FEmotions came later when we were
OL,15,Funable to resuscitate the child. " she
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,18,F"Here was a child who had been killed
OL,19,Fin broad daylight."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/14
