OL,3,C20 Days in Mariupol: Nurse recounts
OL,4,Cfinal days before Russian occupation
OL,6,FBut despite the increasingly tense
OL,7,Fatmosphere as Russian troops
OL,8,Fsurrounded the city, Olena kept
OL,9,Fworking.
OL,11,FOn March 3 - as more bombs rained down
OL,12,Fon the city and also her home - Olena
OL,13,Fbrought her husband, daughter, and two
OL,14,Fyoung grandchildren, to live in the
OL,15,Fhospital.
OL,17,FHer grandchildren, aged 18 months and
OL,18,Fthree years old, slept on the hospital
OL,19,Ffloor in a small storage room.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/14
