OL,6,FMeanwhile, hospital patients and Olena
OL,7,Fherself slept in the corridors to stay
OL,8,Faway from windows in case they
OL,9,Fexploded.
OL,11,F"There was no water, no electricity,
OL,12,Fno communication. We were like in a
OL,13,Ftrance," she said, adding that they
OL,14,Fonly charged their phones to use their
OL,15,Fflashlights during operations.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/14
