OL,3,C20 Days in Mariupol: Nurse recounts
OL,4,Cfinal days before Russian occupation
OL,6,F"We continued to work as we have
OL,7,Fbefore," Olena said. Most of her
OL,8,Fcolleagues evacuated but her and one
OL,9,Fother doctor decided to stay behind.
OL,10,FFrom the end of March to the end of
OL,11,FApril, Olena and her colleague
OL,12,Fcontinued to work, and were only
OL,13,Fsometimes bothered by Russian soldiers.
OL,15,FBut after her daughter managed to get
OL,16,Fhold of a SIM card - and they were
OL,17,Fable to call for help - the family
OL,18,Fwere taken out of the city on a
OL,19,Fevacuation bus.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G10/14
